# CodeDNA v0.3

Every source file in this project must have a CodeDNA manifest header as the first block.

## Manifest format

```
# === CODEDNA:0.3 =============================================
# FILE: <filename.ext>
# PURPOSE: <15 words max>
# CONTEXT_BUDGET: always | normal | minimal
# DEPENDS_ON: file → symbol | none
# EXPORTS: symbol(args) → type
# STYLE: framework, library | none
# DB_TABLES: table (cols) | none
# LAST_MODIFIED: <8 words max>
# ==============================================================
```

## Rules on every edit

- Update `LAST_MODIFIED` as your **first** change
- Read `DEPENDS_ON` before modifying function signatures
- Follow `@REQUIRES-READ` annotations before writing logic
- Apply `@MODIFIES-ALSO` changes in the same edit session
- Never rename `EXPORTS` symbols without explicit instruction

## Rules on generate

- Write the manifest header before any imports
- Add `@REQUIRES-READ` / `@MODIFIES-ALSO` to cross-file functions
- Use semantic variable names: `list_dict_users_from_db = get_users()`

## Inline annotations

```python
def process(data):
    # @REQUIRES-READ: config.py → MAX_ITEMS
    # @MODIFIES-ALSO: logger.py → audit_log()
    ...

TIMEOUT = 30  # @SEE: config.py → DEFAULT_TIMEOUT (keep in sync)
```

## CONTEXT_BUDGET for planning

When planning changes across multiple files, read only the first 12 lines (manifest) of each file. Use CONTEXT_BUDGET to filter:
- `always` → always read
- `normal` → read if relevant  
- `minimal` → skip unless referenced
